<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Film Awards Presented </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The 16th Hong Kong Film Awards
were presented here tonight at Hong Kong Cultural Center, with
"Comrade, Almost a Love Story" being a big winner.
</P>
<P>
The movie, which gained 11 nominations, won nine awards,
including the best picture, best director, best screenplay and
best actress.
</P>
<P>
The best actress went to Maggie Cheung, who had gained the
title twice in 1990 and 1993 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Kent Cheng, who starred in a movie about police, beat all the
other nominees to obtain the best actor.
</P>
<P>
A total of 15 awards were presented at today's ceremony, the
last one before Hong Kong returns to China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
