<HEADLINE> French Interns, Private Doctors Demonstrate in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of interns, externs,
private doctors and insurance workers demonstrated today in Paris
to protest government budgetary cut in social security programs
and call for protection of "quality medical treatment."
</P>
<P>
Police said 8,600 took part in the demonstration, while the
organizers claimed 60,000, in the fifth demonstration staged by
the interns and private doctors since they began a strike nearly
five weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The protesters took the Hippocrate Oath at the Bastille Square
to show their belief in professional quality of medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
The protest was triggered by a government plan to establish a
convention for all hospitals and private doctors which will punish
those who over-spend.
</P>
<P>
The interns said that although they don't oppose medical
budgetary reform, they think that the measure would restrict
doctors' professional practice to provide quality treatment for
their patients. 
</P>
</TEXT>
