<HEADLINE> China to Send 275 Athletes For 2nd East Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- China will send a total of 275
athletes, including 42 Atlanta Olympians, to take part in the 2nd
East Asian Games slated from May 10-19 in Pusan, South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Olympic gold medalists Sun Fuming, Zhan Xugang and Tang
Lingsheng are among the roster, Wu Shouzhang, head of the Chinese
sports delegation which consists of 396 members, told a news
conference on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sun claimed the first gold medal in the women's over 72-kg judo
competition for China at the Centennial Olympic Games last
summer. Weightlifter Zhan shattered the world mark in the men's
70-kg category en route to winning the Olympic title, while his
teammate Tang chalked up the 54-kg title.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,600 athletes from China, Japan, the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea, South Korea, Kazakhstan, Mongolia, Guam, Hong
Kong, Chinese Taipei, Macao hav decided to participate in the
10-day, 13-sport games, which include athletics, swimming, judo,
badminton, basketball, soccer, boxing, gymnastics, wresting,
Taekwondo, Wushu, soft tennis, weightlifting.
</P>
<P>
The first East Asian Games was held in Shanghai in 1993 when
China collected 105 golds, 74 silvers and 34 bronzes out of 168
events. Japan was second in the tally with 25-37-55. 
</P>
</TEXT>
