<HEADLINE> Drug Abuse Among Japanese Students up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Police have discovered 274 cases of
suspected violation of the Stimulants Control Law by youths aged
between 14 and 19 in the first two months of this year, up 53.9
percent over the same period of last year, the Japanese news
agency said today.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the number of senior high school students police
discovered using stimulant drugs stood at 214, Kyodo quoted police
as saying. 
