<HEADLINE> GCC Data Center to Start Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 14 (Xinhua) -- An economic data center
linking all the data services in the six Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) states will come into operation and start
providing services to all subscribers all over the world by the
end of this year.
</P>
<P>
General Director of Kuwaiti Commerce and Industry Chamber
Ahmad Rashid Al-Haroun told reporters today that the data center
would be established in the General Secretariat of the GCC
Chambers Union based in Saudi Arabia and it would be completed by
the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said the center would be linked with other data centers in
GCC chambers as a network via satellite.
</P>
<P>
The data network, which serves individuals and all sectors,
will provide all information through the Internet in both
English and Arabic languages to enable subscribers all over the
world to benefit from the service, Al-Haroun said.
</P>
<P>
The data network in the Gulf is the first of its kind that
links all GCC states and serves subscribers in and outside the
area.
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic organization,
groups Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Kuwait, Oman,
Qatar and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait recently signed an agreement in Saudi Arabia with the
General Secretariat of the GCC Chambers Union to support the
establishment, operation and maintenance of the data center,
Al-Haroun said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
