<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Defense Ministers Confer on Military Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian said here today the current visit of the Russian Minister
of National Defense Igor Nikolayevich Rodionov to China is
conducive to maintaining and developing the friendship between the
armed forces of the two countries, and to the all-round growth
of bilateral ties as well.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission
and a state councillor, made the remark during talks with
Rodionov, who arrived in Beijing Monday evening at Chi's
invitation.
</P>
<P>
Chi said the growth of the Sino-Russian relations is "in the
fundamental interests of the people of both countries," and is
also "conducive to peace, stability, and development of the
Asia-Pacific and the world as a whole."
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to usher in the 21st century together with the
Russian friends and act in accordance with the Five Principles of
Peaceful Coexistence, to enable our two countries to become good
neighbors, good partners, and good friends forever and to push
forward the strategic cooperative partnership between our two
countries," Chi said.
</P>
<P>
With the growth of the friendship between the two nations,
the Chinese defense minister said, the ties between their armed
forces is developing steadily.
</P>
<P>
He said in recent years, the two sides have made friendly
exchanges at various levels and in various areas. Senior officials
of the armies of the two countries have maintained friendly
contacts, and fruitful cooperation has been conducted in many
specialized areas, he added.
</P>
<P>
Chi expressed the hope that the armed forces of China and
Russia would maintain the momentum of high-level exchanges, and
step up military cooperation in various fields so as to further
the friendship between them.
</P>
<P>
Chi also briefed the Russian visitors on the building of
China's armed forces and its defense-oriented defense policy.
</P>
<P>
Rodionov, who is on his first trip to China as minister of
national defense, said the mutual trust between China and Russia
established through dialogue has set a good example for the rest
of the world to follow.
</P>
<P>
The establishment and advancement of their strategic
cooperative partnership that caters to the needs of the 21st
century entirely complies to the interests of the two countries
and two peoples, and is also conducive to the stability and peace
of the Asia-Pacific region and the world, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Rodionov spoke highly of the smooth growth of the friendly
cooperation between the armed forces of the two countries. This
mutually beneficial cooperation is not directed at a third nation,
he said, adding that it will help increase the understanding and
trust between the two countries and two peoples and enhance the
regional and global peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Chi presided over a ceremony to welcome Rodionov this morning,
and hosted a dinner in the Russian defense minister's honor this
evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
