<HEADLINE> Importance of Agricultural Industrialization Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Agricultural industrialization, a
creation of farmers, is the basis for modernizing agriculture and
should get more attention from the government, said a senior
official during an inspection in east China's Jiangsu province
over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The key to agricultural industrialization is to bring
agro-products into the market and make farmers become the main
force in the market, said Li Tieying, member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party
(CPC) and state councillor.
</P>
<P>
"We must encourage the farmer to enter the market in order to
push forward the pace of agro-industrialization," Li said, adding
that the idea of the market should be introduced to rural
households so that farmers could be closely connected with the
changing market.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the central government has always attached great
importance to agro-industrialization. The central agriculture
working conference held last year has mapped out plans to promote
agro-industrialization. The plan is being carried out smoothly
throughout the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li urged provinces known as agro-giants in the country to make
the breakthrough in developing agriculture and enhancing growth of
the rural economy. He said that agro-industrialization should be
outlined in local five-year plans (1996-2000) as a strategy of
stimulating development of local economy. 
</P>
