<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Navy serviceman stationed at
the Misawa air base in northeastern Japan was indicted today for
attempting to rape and injuring a Japanese woman, a news report
said today.
</P>
<P>
Chief Petty Officer Raymond Cunningham, 39, was taken by
Japanese authorities from U.S. military authorities following the
indictment, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The indictment said that Cunningham assaulted the woman in her
30s in a rape attempt in a fishing port city of Hachinohe, Aomori
Prefecture on March 21.
</P>
<P>
The woman was knocked to the ground and struck about the face
and injured.
</P>
<P>
Cunningham acknowledged he assaulted the woman while under
stress from his job, Japanese prosecutors were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The incident is another assault on Japanese woman by
U.S. serviceman based in Japan in recent weeks, a similar incident
occurred at Yokosuka naval base in Kanagawa Prefecture on April 3.
</P>
<P>
Such incidents have caused strong opposition to the
U.S. military presence in Japan among local residents. 
