<HEADLINE> Mexican Zaragoza Defends WBC Junior Featherweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Daniel Zaragoza of Mexico defended
his World Boxing Council junior featherweight title Monday in
Osaka with a unanimous 12-round decision over challenger Joichiro
Tatsuyoshi of Japan.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth title defense for the champion. He won the
crown from Hector Acero of Dominican Republic on November 5, 1995,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Judge Lou Filippo of the United States scored it 115-112 for
Zaragoza. Tony Castellano of the United States had it 116-111 and
Rolando Barrovecchio of Italy scored it 116-112 for Zaragoza.
</P>
<P>
It was Zaragoza's second victory over Tatsuyoshi. In the title
match in Yokohama near Tokyo on March 1996, Zaragoza stopped
Tatsuyoshi in the 11th round.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Zaragoza collected a total of 55 victories,
including 27 knockouts, against seven defeats and three
draws. Tatsuyoshi has a record of 13 victories against four
defeats and one draw. 
</P>
