<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese National
People's Congress (NPC) Chairman Qiao Shi said today that China
will, as always, respect Mongolia's independence and sovereignty,
as well as its people's own choice for their road of development.
</P>
<P>
At a dinner given in his honor by Radnaasumberel Gonchigdorj,
chairman of Mongolia's State Great Hural, the country's
parliament, Qiao said China attaches great importance to
developing friendly relations with Mongolia, an important neighbor.
</P>
<P>
China and Mongolia, Qiao said, are friendly neighbors linked
by mountains and rivers and their exchanges and cooperation have
expanded over the last few years.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and people are willing to push forward,
with the Mongolian government and people, friendly and
good-neighborly relations on the basis of the five principles of
peaceful co-existence and the China-Mongolia Treaty of
Friendly Relations and Cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
The top Chinese legislator hoped his visit would deepen
understanding, promote friendship and enhance relations between
China and Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Chairman Gonchigdori said China is an influential country in
the world and its peaceful foreign policy is an important
factor guaranteeing peace, stability and development in the
Aisa-Pacific region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Developing friendly and good-neighborly relations with China,
just as in the past, will be one of the main planks of Mongolia's
foreign policy, the Mongolian parliamentary leader said.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia is the last stop of Qiao's European and Asian tour,
which has already taken him to France, Norway and Italy. It is
also the first visit to Mongolia by a Chinese NPC chairman.
</P>
