<HEADLINE> China's Air Force to Be Equipped with State-of-Art (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the Korean War, the Chinese Air Force brought down 330
American planes and damaged 95, according to General Liu.
</P>
<P>
After decades of development, the Chinese Air Force has
localized most of its equipment, with a large number of
self-designed and Chinese-made high-quality fighters, attackers,
bombers, reconnaissance planes, and special-purpose planes, Liu
noted.
</P>
<P>
To support the air force weaponry system, the Air Force has
been equipped with sophisticated air-to-air missiles, air-borne
radars, fire control systems, communications and guidance
facilities, and flying control systems, he noted.
</P>
<P>
With 76 percent of its pilots being able to fly all-weather and
a flying safety for 16 years running, the Air Force is developing
an advanced air defense system equipped with a complete set of
high-range, medium-range, low-range, long-range and short-range
missiles, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Air Force is now able to fight both defense and
offense battles under high-tech conditions," the Chinese general
noted.
</P>
<P>
"Over the next few years the Chinese Air Force will enhance its
deterrent force in the air, ability to impose air blockades and
launch air strikes, as well as the ability to conduct joint
operations of ground forces, navy and the air force," he said.
</P>
