<HEADLINE> Chinese, Iranian Foreign Ministers Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen met with Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister
Alaedin Boroujerdi here today.
</P>
<P>
Boroujerdi said that Sino-Iranian relations have seen a healthy
development in recent years, with frequent personnel exchanges and
growing links in the fields of politics and economy.
</P>
<P>
He said that there is still great potential for the development
of bilateral relations. He pointed out that strengthening its
relations with China is one of the fixed policies of the Iranian
government. He believes that with the joint efforts of the two
countries, the existing friendly cooperative relations will be
further promoted.
</P>
<P>
He briefed Qian about Iran's efforts to improve and develop
relations with other Islamic countries. He said that Iran will
continue to work for enhancing the solidarity of the Islamic
countries. The recent visits by state leaders of Iran to a number
of Arab countries have achieved positive results, he told Qian.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the two countries share a tradition of
friendship. He said that China is ready to work with Iran to
further develop bilateral relations on the basis of equality,
mutual interest, and the five principles of peaceful co-existence.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation on Iran's efforts to improve its
relations with other Islamic countries, especially its
neighbors. He stressed that differences between countries should
be resolved through peaceful discussion on the basis of mutual
respect, mutual understanding, and mutual accommodation. He said
that the cordial relations among all countries and their common
development benefit the peace and development of different regions
and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Boroujerdi arrived in Beijing this morning. He held talks with
Chinese Deputy Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan earlier today.
</P>
