<HEADLINE> Panizzi Leads in Spanish Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Gilles Panizzi of France took a
surprise lead on the opening day of the Spanish Rally Monday in
Lloret De Mar as the Peugeot team upstaged the main championship
challengers.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Francois Delecour led Peugeot team mate Panizzi for
the two opening stages.
</P>
<P>
But Delecour made a mistake on the third stage, the
10-kilometer Les Llosses run, and ran off the road. He lost more
than two minutes and dropped out of the top 10.
</P>
<P>
Panizzi kept up his advantage to extend a lead over the
Mitsubishi of reigning world champion Tommi Makinen of Finland to
16 seconds by the end of the fourth stage.
</P>
<P>
Briton Colin McRae was in third place, just one second behind
Makinen. Italy's Piero Liatti, who suffered a puncture on the
opening stage, recovered to end the fourth stage in fourth
position overall, just one second behind McRae. 
</P>
