<HEADLINE> Northeast China City Exports Vegetables, Fruits to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Mudanjiang in northeast China's
Heilongjiang Province exported some 180,000 tons of fruits and
vegetables to Russia last year.
</P>
<P>
Water melon, wild cabbage, and apricot were among the most
popular exports.
</P>
<P>
The largest base in China to export vegetables and fruits to
Russia, the city has over 80 border trade companies which have
signed contracts with local fruit and vegetable planters.
</P>
<P>
The city has also set up more than 40 wholesale markets in the
far eastern areas in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Neighboring Russia, Mudanjiang has a comparatively higher
temperature and more rains that favors planting fruits and
vegetables.  
</P>
</TEXT>
