<HEADLINE> Zairean Rebels Capture Kananga Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Zairean rebels have captured
the town of Kananga, capital of Western Kasai Province and one
of the largest towns outside Kinshasa.
</P>
<P>
The town fell to the rebel forces on Saturday, a report
reaching here this morning said, quoting Voice of the People
Radio broadcast from the eastern town of Goma, where the rebel
headquarters is located.
</P>
<P>
The fall of Kananga leaves the rebels in a good position to
move on Bandundu, about 270 km northeast of the Zairean capital
Kinshasa, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The rebels of the Alliance of Democratic Forces for the
Liberation of Congo-Zaire, led by Laurent Kabila, took arms
last October to topple President Mobutu Sese Seko. In less than
six months, they have occupied two thirds of Africa's third
largest country.
</P>
<P>
The rebels seized the country's diamond capital Mbuji-Mayi
on April 5 and the second largest city of Lubumbashi on the
Zairean-Zambian border on April 9, thus controling the
country's valuable mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
Rebels said on Sunday they were resuming their offensive after
a three-day halt called to give President Mobutu time to resign.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the rebel forces are marching forward to the
Zairean capital Kishasa from two directions, by using the Zaire
River in the north and from the Mbuji-Mayi-Kananga axis in the
east.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the rebel forces are just 300 km away
from the capital. enditem

