<HEADLINE> Ecological Science Publicity Book Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on a newly published
ecological science publicity book has been held in Beijing,
today's China Forestry News Reported.
</P>
<P>
The book, named "Earth -- Our Common Home," aims to introduce
basic ecological knowledge to China's younger generation and
increase young people's awareness of environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
"The youth and children will be the masters of the earth in
the 21st century, and they will bring hope to a greener and
cleaner world," the authors said.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 people attended the seminar, including Lei
Jieqiong, vice-chairwoman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress. 
</P>
