<HEADLINE> India to Get Aid From ADB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 14 (Xinhua) -- India is likely to get a total
of 820 million U.S. dollars in assistance from the Asian
Development Bank (ADB) during 1997 compared with the 592 million
dollars it received last year, the Press Trust of India said
today.
</P>
<P>
The aid was announced by ADB resident representative Shigeko M.
Asher while addressing a seminar here today.
</P>
<P>
She said the bank has targeted to provide 250 million dollars
exclusively for housing development in India's urban areas.
</P>
