<HEADLINE> First Bridal Photography Show Held In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 bridal photography
companies have gathered here for the first time at a show targeted
at the pockets of newlyweds in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Met with non-stop enthusiasm for their goods and services, the
companies each took in some 100 orders a day during the five-day
show, which ended today. Each order is valued at 2000-10,000 yuan,
according to Liu Sheng, an organizer of the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that that local Beijing companies, which represent the
majority of those in the wedding photo profession, make up only
some 40 percent of the total number of the participants.
</P>
<P>
The rest are from Beijing-based companies funded by Hong Kong,
Taiwan and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Beijing residents have been less inclined to
throw lavish banquets at weddings and are becoming generous --
spending one or two months' salary or even more -- on bridal
photography.
</P>
<P>
Some of the romantic photographs are as large as a full-sized
calendar.
</P>
<P>
There are 100,000 marriages reported in Beijing annually,
according to statistics of the Beijing Civil Affairs Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Bridal photography originated in Japan in the 1970s, and
flourished in Taiwan. The first Taiwan-Beijing joint bridal
photography venture was established in 1989, which invigorated the
stagnant Beijing bridal photography market.
</P>
<P>
There are currently more than 300 businesses engaged in bridal
photography in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
More than a dozen companies handling tourism, diamond, bridal
wear, photo frames and design also participated in the fair, which
was sponsored by the China Light Industrial Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
