<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Down on Late Selling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
weaker against the U.S. dollar today, as a spate of selling by
local and Asian players took its toll on the currency in late
dealings.
</P>
<P>
It closed at 78.17 U.S. cents, compared to 78.59 on Friday's
close.
</P>
<P>
Traders said sellers were taking profits on a strong Australian
dollar/Japanese yen exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
"Basically it was Australian dollar/yen selling throughout the
day above 99.00 yen," said St. George Bank foreign exchange
trading manager Stuart Moore.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 98.82 against the yen from 97.71
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
And it was at 1.3431 from 1.3327 against the Deutsche mark.
</P>
</TEXT>
