<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Macao Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen
said here today that Macao's return to the motherland has been on
the agenda since less than three years remain until its return.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark during a meeting here this afternoon with Ma
Man-kei, president of Chinese General Chamber of Commerce in
Macao, and his party who are attending a forum to commemorate the
fourth anniversary of the promulgation of the Basic Law of the
Macao Special Administrative Region and the 10th anniversary of
the signing of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration on the
Question of Macao.
</P>
<P>
Qian said it is imperative to strengthen cooperation between
the governments of China and Portugal based on the implementation
the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration.
</P>
<P>
The Macao compatriots should further bring into full play the
spirit of loving the country and Macao and involve more in the
work during the later transitional period and make efforts for
Macao's stable transition and smooth transfer of the power so as
to establish a special administrative region with a high-degree of
autonomy, said Qian.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted slow progress in solving the localization of civil
servants and law as well as status for official Chinese language
and expressed the hope that the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison
Group will accelerate the work.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government is concerned about the
provisional issues related to Macao's public security and economy,
hoping that the Portuguese side will earnestly assume the
responsibility in this regard during its transitional period.
</P>
<P>
After Hong Kong's return to the motherland, Qian said economic
ties between Hong Kong and Macao will be closer. "We will
encourage Hong Kong, Macao, and China's inland areas to strengthen
their economic ties".
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that with the concerted efforts of the
Macao compatriots, Macao's economy is bound to grow.
</P>
<P>
Ma said that under the care of the mainland people, Macao is
stable in society during its transitional period and its people
have boosted confidence in its future.
</P>
<P>
The work for the localization of civil servants and law and
status for official Chinese language should be done in an
accelerating way, said Ma.
</P>
<P>
Ma said he was sure that in the coming two years or more, the
Macao compatriots will, as always, unite under the banner of
loving the country and Macao, and contribute to the realization of
its stable transition and a smooth transfer of the power.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Qian also answered a number of questions
raised by the visitors.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ping, director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of
the State Council, also met with Ma Man-kei and his party at the
Great Hall of the people here this morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
