<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Meets Burundian Presidential Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister
Qian Qichen met with Leonidas Havyarimana, special envoy of the
President of Burundi, here today.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Diaoyutai State Guest House, Qian
said that the two countries enjoy a good relationship. He said
that China has been closely watching the situation in Burundi and
is delighted to see that the Central African nation is progressing
toward peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
He said that a country has to maintain political stability in
order to achieve economic growth and improve the living standards
of its people.
</P>
<P>
Havyarimana, state secretary in charge of cooperation in the
Ministry of External Relations and Cooperation of Burundi, briefed
Qian on the current situation in the country. He expressed
gratitude to Qian for China's consistent support and assistance to
Burundi. He also handed over a letter from President Buyoya to
Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Havyarimana arrived in Beijing for a good-will visit this
morning. Before his meeting with Qian, he had held talks with
Assistant Foreign Minister Ji Peiding this afternoon. The two
sides exchanges views on bilateral relations and issues of common
concern.  
</P>
