<HEADLINE> Forum to Mark Anniversary of Macao Basic Law and Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A forum was held today in the
Great Hall of the People in Beijing to mark the 4th anniversary of
the promulgation of the Basic Law of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) and the 10th anniversary of the
signing of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration.
</P>
<P>
Participants, who are from various circles of the inland areas
and Macao, agreed that the Basic Law and the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Declaration are focused on the implementation of the principles of
"one country, two systems", "Macao people governing Macao," and a
high-degree of autonomy in Macao, which will be a special
administrative region of China.
</P>
<P>
They believe Deng Xiaoping's great concept of "one country, two
systems" will surely come true if the two documents are strictly
carried out.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at the forum, Lu Ping, director of the Hong
Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council, expressed
satisfaction over the development of friendly relations between
China and Portugal and their cooperation on the Macao question in
the past decade.
</P>
<P>
"Macao has maintained a stable society, and a continuous
economic development. As each piece of work in the transitional
period is in smooth progress, people are much more confident about
Macao's future," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the "one country, two systems" principle is the
most essential factor for Hong Kong and Macao to maintain their
stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
It greatly inspires the people's confidence and guarantees a
splendid future for the two regions, he added.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the "one country, two systems" concept, put forward
by late Deng Xiaoping, "not only complies with the current trend
of peace and progress, but also accords with the practical
situations of Hong Kong and Macao."
</P>
<P>
"It not only guarantees the country's reunification and
territorial integrity, but also maintains the stability,
development, and prosperity of Hong Kong and Macao."
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, it wins the support from all the Chinese people
including Hong Kong and Macao residents, and draws widespread
attention from the international community," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
