<HEADLINE> Forum to Mark Anniversary of Macao Basic Law and Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Referring to the tasks concerning the maintenance of Macao's
stability and prosperity as well as the smooth transition, Lu said
these tasks include the further study and promotion of the Basic
Law, the formation of the Preparatory Committee of the Macao SAR,
the participation in affairs in Macao's transitional period, and
the stability and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Lu also said the Preparatory Committee of the Macao SAR has an
important job to implement the Basic Law and decisions of the
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Unlike Hong Kong, a preliminary working committee for the
Preparatory Committee is unnecessary, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ma Man-kei, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, said the
signing of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration has smoothly
settled the Macao question left from history, and gives an example
for solving international disputes in a peaceful way through
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
He said the smooth return of Macao is the people's will and the
current trend.
</P>
<P>
Although there are some difficult matters, "I believe they are
sure to be solved, as long as China and Portugal stick to the
stipulations of the Joint Declaration, follow in the direction in
line with the Basic Law, stand firmly on the development and
stability of Macao and the interests of the local residents, and
keep in accordance with a spirit of mutual understanding," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ma also expressed the hope that the majority of Macao residents
and people in the various circles will unite under the banner of
love of country and Macao, and contribute to the stable transition
of Macao as well as the smooth transfer of power.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at the forum, Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua
News Agency Macao Branch, reviewed the work done by the people in
the various circles of Macao and the social organizations there to
promote the Basic Law in the past four years.
</P>
<P>
As a national law, the Basic Law of the Macao SAR must be
abided by not only by Macao residents, but also by people in the
inland areas, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Today's forum was held by the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office of the State Council. Chen Ziying, vice-director of the
office, presided over the forum.
</P>
<P>
Also attending today's forum were Vice-Chairman of the National
People's Congress Standing Committee Lei Jieqiong; Vice-Chairmen
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference National
Committee Qian Weichang, and Wan Guoquan; and some officials from
relevant departments. 
</P>
