<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Volumes Up, Prices Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's
re-exports in January this year increased by 2.6 percent over a
year earlier, while that of domestic exports decreased by 7.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the Census and Statistics Department, taken
together, the volume of total exports increased by 1.0 percent.
Meanwhile, the volume of imports increased by 3.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the three months ending January 1997 with the three
months ending January 1996, the volume of re-exports and imports
increased by 5.5 and 5.1 percent, respectively. However, the
volume of domestic exports dropped by 7.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing January 1997 with January 1996, the prices of
re-exports and domestic exports decreased by 1.3 and 1.5 percent
respectively. Meanwhile, import prices decreased by 2.4 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
