<DOCNO> XIE19970414.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Lantau Link to Open to Traffic in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The doubled-decked Lantau Link,
comprising two major bridges and a viaduct, will open to traffic
in May.
</P>
<P>
The link is built as part of the 34-kilometer transport
corridor to the new international airport under construction at
Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
Traffic will be carried on a dual three-lane expressway on the
open upper deck. In case of bad weather, traffic can be diverted
to two single-lane carriage ways on the sheltered lower deck,
which will also carry the airport railway.
</P>
<P>
Vehicles using the link will have to pay tolls, at a toll plaza
located on the Lantau side.
</P>
<P>
Both bridges are the largest of their kind to carry road and
rail traffic. The Tsing Ma Bridge, spanning the marine channel
between Tsing Yi and Ma Wan islands, has a central span of 1,377
meters while the cable-stayed Kap Shui Mun Bridge, which connects
Ma Wan and Lantau island, has a main span of 430 meters.
</P>
<P>
Secretary for Works Kwong Hong-sang said that Hong Kong has
never built such long-span bridges before.
</P>
<P>
He said that it has been a great achievement, considering that
the two contracts to build the bridges were only awarded in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The Lantau Link and its associated road network have been
designated as a control area, to maintain safe and efficient traffic
operations on it.
</P>
<P>
The control area is equipped with a sophisticated
computer-based Traffic Control and Surveillance System.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is the first time that a system of this kind
covers such a large area. The system contains a log of
state-of-the-art techniques and in many ways it is one of the most
advanced systems in the world.
</P>
<P>
The control area includes about 17 kilometers of the airport
transport corridor stretching from the Mei Foo Interchange at the
start of the Kwai Chung Viaduct section of Route 3 to the Yam O
Interchange on the North Lantau Expressway.
</P>
<P>
The main control center is housed in the North West Tsing Yi
Administration Building. The system's equipment includes closed
circuit television, automatic incident detector, automatic weight
detectors, environmental sensors, emergency telephones, vehicle
overweight detectors, variable traffic signs, land control signals
and radio re-broadcast facilities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
