<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Hits Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on the
Richter scale hit Surigao City, the southern Philippines, this
afternoon, but no damage and aftershocks are expected, the
Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology said.
</P>
<P>
In a preliminary report, the institute said the tremor of
moderate strength occurred at 16:24 (08:24 GMT) but no damage has
been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was 74 kilometers northeast of Surigao City,
where extremely feeble shocks were felt by residents, it said.
</P>
<P>
Earthquakes measuring 5 to 6 on the Richter scale usually are
felt over wide areas and some of them cause local damage near the
epicenter.  
</P>
