<HEADLINE> Bohai Shipyard to Build 100,000-Ton Shipway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- China's State Planning Commission
has just approved the building of a shipway for vessels of 100,000
DWT at the Bohai Shipyard, one of the four largest shipbuilding
enterprises in the country.
</P>
<P>
The project involves a total investment of nearly 200 million
yuan. Once construction is complete by the end of next year, the
shipway will be able to accommodate the building of 2.5
vessels of 100,000 DWT per year, the China State Shipbuilding
Corporation says.
</P>
<P>
The shipyard has so far finished basic designs for the shipway
and a dyke-closing project.
</P>
<P>
The Bohai Shipyard is located in the city of Huludao, in
northeast China's Liaoning Province. Huludao, near the Liaodong
gulf of the Bohai Sea, is an important city in the booming Bohai
economic rim. Shipbuilding has become a pillar industry for
Huludao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
