<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lu Ping on Preparatory Committee of Macao SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The formation of the Preparatory
Committee of the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) is a
major job concerning the return of Macao, but the establishment of
a preliminary working committee is not necessary.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ping, director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of
the State Council, made the remark in a speech at a forum to
mark the 4th anniversary of the promulgation of the Basic Law of
the Macao SAR and the 10th anniversary of the signing of the
Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration.
</P>
<P>
He said the formation of the Preparatory Committee of the Macao
SAR is an important task for implementing the Basic Law and
relevant stipulations of the National People's Congress, and has
drawn widespread attention of the public.
</P>
<P>
Unlike Hong Kong, a preliminary working committee for the
Preparatory Committee is unnecessary, he said, adding that all
matters concerning the formation of the Macao SAR will be
submitted to the Preparatory Committee for study and discussion.
</P>
<P>
Although more than two years remain before Macao's return, the
time is still pressing, he said.
</P>
<P>
Lu said Macao is a small place, but it will be the same as Hong
Kong in pursuing the principle of "one country, two systems" and
the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Work done by the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong
SAR also needs to be done by the Preparatory Committee of the
Macao SAR, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said the Preparatory Committee of the Macao SAR can draw on
the experiences of the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong SAR,
but Macao has its own characteristics, and must, like Hong Kong,
deal with some difficult matters.
</P>
<P>
In order to ensure the smooth operation of the Preparatory
Committee, it is appropriate to make some preparations in advance,
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
