<HEADLINE> Share Prices On Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index fell by 33.84 points to close at 2,034.64 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 141.64 million units, worth
429.85 million Singapore dollars (about 298.51 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 331 to 29, while 247
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Wing Tai was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 7.95 million units. It was followed by the Development
Bank of Singapore (DBS) Land which had 7.45 million shares traded.
The Hong Kong Land was next with 6.75 million of its shares
changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Land led the gainers of the day as it rose by 25
cents to finish at 7.15 Singapore dollars. OUE increased by 15
cents to end at 6.65 Singapore dollars, while the Asean Fund,
Singapore Airlines Foreign and Wing Tai gained 10 cents each to
close at 16.6 US dollars, 11.9 Singapore dollars and 4.06 dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign A was
the biggest loser of the day as it declined by 60 cents to end at
14.7 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 and the Malaya Banking 200
fell by 50 cents each to close at 16.7 and 14.8 Singapore dollars
respectively.  
</P>
