<HEADLINE> Johannesburg Banks Suffer Greatly in Robberies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Robbers have struck at least
43 banks in the Johannesburg area since the beginning of this year,
the local daily the Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
Accurate figures on losses are not available following a media
black-out agreement made between banks and police last year, but
conservative estimates place them at more than five million Rands,
(1.14 million U.S. dollars), the report said.
</P>
<P>
While most major banks have fallen victim to the gangs in the
past months, Nedbank and Trust Bank, two well-known banks in
Johannesburg, have been affected in the worst, with 10 and four hits
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The impact on morale is increasingly being felt with employees
refusing to do teller duties unless better security measures are
introduced, the report quoted informed sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bank robberies, together with rapes and hijackings, were declared
priority crimes last year and police and the Council of South African
Banks have joined forces to combat bank bandits. enditem

