litigations since 1994 by advance fee fraud victims, the report
said, adding that the Nigerian bank has to seek redress from
appellate courts in these countries.
</P>
<P>
Those foreign nationals fell victims of fraudsters because
they were greedy and were themselves culpable, being accomplices
in plots to defraud Nigeria, a official of the bank was quoted as
saying. 
