<HEADLINE> HK's Re-exports Up Slightly, Domestic Exports Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
re-exports grew by 0.3 percent in February 1997 over a year
earlier to 76.5 billion HK dollars (9.87 billion US dollars),
according to the figures released here today by the Census and
Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports decreased by 11 percent to 12.6
billion HK dollars (1.63 billion US dollars) while the value of
imports increased by 6.6 percent to 102.3 billion HK dollars (13.2
billion US dollars) in February.
</P>
<P>
The value of re-exports in the first two months of 1997
increased slightly by 0.6 percent to 178.6 billion HK dollars (23
billion US dollars) over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The value in the period decreased by 10 percent to 29.9 billion
HK dollars (3.86 billion US dollars) over the same period in 1996
while the value of imports in the first two months of 1997
decreased by 3.4 percent to 234 billion HK dollars (30.2 billion
US dollars) over the same period in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
