<HEADLINE> HKSAR PLC President Welcomes Right of Abode Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Rita Fan, president of the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), today welcomed the statement by the
Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the Chinese State Council
detailing the policies in respect of Hong Kong residents'
nationality and right of abode.
</P>
<P>
Fan reiterated that the issue of the right of abode of Hong
Kong permanent residents of the HKSAR was extremely important, and
that it needed to be resolved as soon as possible so that the
worries of Hong Kong people living in the territory and abroad
could be alleviated.
</P>
<P>
She said that once the Chief Executive's Office submitted the
draft right of abode bill to the PLC for passage, the council
would commence to scrutinize the bill and ensure that the
procedure of three readings of the bill be completed before June
30, 1997, so that Hong Kong people could be certain of the details
of the relevant legislation as early as possible.
</P>
<P>
She added that the legislation would then be confirmed on July
1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
She said she believed as the matter concerned the interest of
every Hong Kong person, the PLC will work in conjunction with the
Chief Executive's Office, and complete the necessary procedures
smoothly and promptly. 
</P>
