<HEADLINE> HKSAR Government Welcomes Right of Abode Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive's Office of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) welcomed the
statement by the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the Chinese
State Council detailing the policies to be adopted on Hong Kong
residents' nationality and right of abode.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Office said that the statement allayed a
concern which had for a considerable time preoccupied the Hong
Kong community and Hong Kong people living abroad.
</P>
<P>
He said the HKSAR government will study the details and prepare
a bill for submission to the Provisional Legislative Council as
soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"We are determined to ensure legislation is completed by July 1
and we hope the Hong Kong government will assist us in this
endeavor, in the interest of the people of Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
