<HEADLINE> Philippines' Ruling Party Begins Election Preparations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- President Fidel Ramos today
ordered his ruling Lakas-NUCD Party to form a committee to
recommend the guidelines, criteria, procedures and timetable for
selecting the party's presidential candidates for the 1998 polls.
</P>
<P>
The move, taken by Ramos who is chairman of the Lakas-NUCD
party, signals the official start of the nomination or
"appointment" process within the party for the May 1998 elections,
according to a press release from the Presidential Press Office.
</P>
<P>
By setting up the committee, Ramos wanted to seek the widest
possible consensus among various geographical and sectoral groups
and political interest blocs within the party as a principal basis
for his choice of the party's standard bearer, the press release
said.
</P>
<P>
The committee will also recommend the guidelines, criteria,
procedures and timetable for the selection of other candidates for
the 1998 national and local polls.
</P>
<P>
These election policy guidelines will be submitted to the Lakas
Party's national directorate within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The party's national directorate will then meet to finalize the
party's general strategy and campaign plan for the 1998 elections.
</P>
<P>
The 16-member committee, chaired by Lakas Party President Raul
Manglapous, will also include Executive Secretary Ruben Torres,
Justice Secretary Teofisto Guingona and presidential assistant for
political affairs Gabriel Claudio.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
