<HEADLINE> Israel Accuses PNA of Smuggling Arms to Prepare for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Israel accused today the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) of smuggling Katyusha
rockets, anti-tank and anti-aircraft missiles in preparation for
future conflicts.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli security official was quoted by the English daily
The Jerusalem Post as saying that the PNA had ambitions to buy
weapons in violation of Oslo peace accords. "They are trying to
get anti-tank and anti-aircraft weapons. There's no problem to
get these things," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the PNA had numerous options to buy cheap rockets and
missiles from Russia and eastern European countries. He noted
that smuggling weapons into the PNA-controlled areas was not
difficult either, because anti-tank and anti-aircraft weapons
were small missiles that can fit into a suitcase.
</P>
<P>
He also suspected the PNA of bringing weapons into Gaza by
fishing boat either from the Mediterranean or from the Sinai
Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Weapons could also be smuggled into the PNA-controlled areas in
the cars of senior Palestinian officials, whose vehicles are
exempt from Israeli security searches, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Although declining to estimate the amount of weapons being
smuggled into PNA self-rule areas, he said the the PNA's aim of
smuggling was not to amass enough weapons to try to defeat Israel
in war, but to upgrade its military capability so that it can
destroy several Israeli tanks in future conflicts to reap
"tremendous propaganda value."
</P>
<P>
Israel is highly sensitive about the alleged PNA's moves to
seek advanced weapons which would threaten its tanks and military
helicopters, Israel's main means of deterrence in the current
confrontation.
</P>
<P>
Following the Palestinian violent protests sparked by Israel's
building of a controversial settlement in East Jerusalem, Israeli
army has deployed tanks, armed personnel carriers and snipers
around major Palestinian cities as a way of deterrence.
</P>
<P>
Israeli officials have also indicated that it would recapture
the Palestinian cities in case of all-out escalation of the
Palestinian violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
