<HEADLINE> Jilin Develops Petrochemical Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's heavy
industrial city of Jilin will highlight petrochemical production
in the next four years.
</P>
<P>
The province will build two petrochemical bases. One, to be
located in the eastern part of the province, is expected to be the
largest organic chemical raw materials and synthetic materials
center in the country.
</P>
<P>
Work to be carried out there includes a project to produce
300,000 tons of synthetic ammonia a year, and an ethylene project
with an annual production capacity of 300,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Another one, in western Jilin, will focus on oil refining and
chemicals based on rich oil and gas resources there.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has listed seven sectors on its
priority list for future development, including oil prospecting
and processing, farm-use chemicals and refined chemicals.
</P>
<P>
Jilin turned out 3.7 million tons of crude oil and processed
7.8 million tons of oil products in 1996.
</P>
<P>
It plans to double its 1995 petrochemical output value by the
year 2000. 
</P>
