<HEADLINE> East China Province Enhances Apartment Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Economically-developed Jiangsu
Province has spent about 4.6 billion yuan on construction of
apartments with a combined floor space of 4.64 million sq m since
1993.
</P>
<P>
Some 70,000 families in the province's urban areas who used to
squeeze in a per capita living space of less than four sq m have
now moved into the newly-built spacious flats.
</P>
<P>
For many years, urban residents, especially families with
moderate and low income, have faced housing difficulties.
Statistics from the early 1990s show that there were more than
70,000 households with a per capita living space of less than four
sq m.
</P>
<P>
To help improve living conditions of these residents and avoid
repeating the past practice of relying on state allotments to
build housing, Since 1993, Jiangsu has redoubled its efforts to
reform the housing system with a range of measures that include
building more open-market flats, setting up a public fund for
housing in the province's 77 cities and county seats, reducing
building costs and offering various kinds of mortgage loans for
housing purchases.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the province has so far pooled 9.3
billion yuan for housing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
