<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolian President Meets Chinese NPC Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President
Punsalmaagiyu Ochirbat said today that his country is willing to
continue to develop friendly relations and expand cooperation with
China on the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks during his meeting with visiting Chairman
of the Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress
(NPC) Qiao Shi.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China and Mongolia are close neighbors and the
Chinese and Mongolian people enjoy traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
Since the normalization of relations between the two countries,
Qiao said, the friendly relations and cooperation between China
and Mongolia have been restored in an all-round way and developed
smoothly in political, economic, cultural and other fields with
efforts by both sides.
</P>
<P>
China has long been attaching great importance to developing
friendly and good-neighborly relations with the surrounding
countries including Mongolia, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the continued consolidation of friendly and
good-neighborly relations between China and Mongolia conforms with
the aspiration and fundamental interests of the two countries and
two peoples.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Mongolia will always be good neighbors
and friends and together usher in a prosperous 21st century no
matter what happens in the world. 
</P>
