<HEADLINE> Preparations For Burundi Summit In Arusha </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Preparations are going on
for the Fourth Great Lakes Region Summit on Burundi, to be held
in Arusha, northern Tanzania, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and
International Co-operation was quoted today by Daily News as
saying that former Tanzanian President Mwalimu Julius Nyerere is
scheduled to submit his report at the summit on the progress made
so far.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the summit would be preceded by a meeting
of the sanctions committee today, while a ministerial technical
committee would meet tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Mwalimu's report was likely to determine the fate
of Burundi, on which an economic embargo was imposed since last July.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere's report will be the basis of deliberations to be made
by the leaders of the Great Lakes Region whether to lift or tighten
the sanctions, he further said.
</P>
<P>
Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda, Rwanda and Zaire imposed sanctions on
Burundi following a military coup in which President Sylvestre
Ntibantunganya was deposed and Major Pierre Buyoya brought back to
power on July 25, last year. 
</P>
