<HEADLINE> Output of Textile Products in Steady Growth in January-February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 14 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics released by
the State Statistics Bureau show that the output of textile
products was in a steady growth during the first two months of
this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, the output of yarns stood at
712,500 tons, up 10.9 percent from that of the corresponding
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
And that of cloth was 2.69 billion meters, a six percent
increase.
</P>
<P>
The output of silk was 8,672 tons, down 11.8 percent from the
corresponding 1996 period, while that of knitting wool reached
60,700 tons, representing a 15.4 percent increase. 
</P>
