<HEADLINE> Mongolian, Chinese Leaders Hail Expanding Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Both Mongolian and Chinese
leaders today agreed that the relations between the two countries
in political, economic, cultural and other fields have greatly
expanded in recent years.
</P>
<P>
This came in the meeting of visiting Chairman Qiao Shi of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC)
with Mongolian Prime Minister Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian prime minister said that relations between
Mongolia and China have developed smoothly and Mongolia regards
its ties with China as one of its major foreign policy principles.
</P>
<P>
He said that Mongolia hopes to develop long-term and stable
relations with China, which are geared towards the 21st century in
accordance with the Mongolia-China Friendly Relations Treaty
signed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia also thanked China for supporting and giving
assistance to Mongolia in the economic development, he added.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Qiao Shi said that the new Mongolian government,
ever since its formation, has attached great importance to
developing friendly relations with China and regards its friendly
ties with China as one of the primary principles of its foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
This policy is a wise and far-sighted policy, Qiao said, the
consolidation and development of friendly and good-neighborly
relations and equal and mutually beneficial cooperation between
the two countries not only conforms with fundamental interests of
both sides but is also China's firm stand.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Mongolia are developing countries and their
economies are complementary and there is a potential for them to
expand economic cooperation and trade, they indicated.
</P>
<P>
They shared the hope that with mutual efforts, the economic
cooperation and trade between the two countries will be pushed to
a new high. 
</P>
