<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Dips Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Prices in India ended the
fiscal 1996-97 (April-March) on a promising note with the annual
rate of inflation falling further to 7.35 percent for the week
ending March 29, The Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
The annual inflation declined by 0.16 percentage points during
the week under review from 7.51 percent for the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The official wholesale price index (WPI) for "all commodities"
(base 1981-82=100) also fell by 0.2 percent to 321.5 (provisional)
as against 322.0 (provisional).
</P>
<P>
This is for the 104th week that prices have maintained single
digit levels.
</P>
<P>
The decline in prices during the week was mainly attributed to
lower prices of commodities such as poultry chicken, eggs, fruits
and vegetables.  
</P>
</TEXT>
