<HEADLINE> Five People Killed by Gale in Poland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and 70
injured as a powerful gale swept across part of Poland over the
weekend, press reports said.
</P>
<P>
The violent storm caused the outbreak of more than 1,000 fires,
destroyed 12,000 substations and cut off kilometers of telephone
wires.
</P>
<P>
A very heavy fall of snow occurred in several provinces and
ports were closed because of the strong winds.
</P>
<P>
Relief aid is being rushed to the stricken areas. 
</P>
