<HEADLINE> Power Outage Hits Many Areas in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 14 (Xinhua) -- A rare power cut hit Jakarta and
its surroundings as well as a number of major cities in Java and
Bali in Indonesia, causing one-day blackout on Sunday, an official
of the state-owned electricity corporation said here last night.
</P>
<P>
The disruption of electrical services on Java and Bali had
created chaos at intersections as most traffic lights were out,
President Director of the state electricity company Djiteng
Marsudi said.
</P>
<P>
"The technical problems interrupted power supply from the
Suralaya power station in the westernmost tip of West Java,"
Djiteng said.
</P>
<P>
The Suralaya power station, with a total supply of 1,600
megawatts, is the single largest generator in Java.
</P>
<P>
Such an electrical problem also happened in November 1994.
</P>
