Prime Minister Sirimavo Bandaranaike in her message said: "as
we  celebrate the New Year, let us all protect and maintain the
national heritage bequeathed to us by forefathers," and "create an
environment where all of us could live in peace and unity as Sri
Lankans."
</P>
<P>
Several Ministers and leaders of major political parties today
also issued their respective messages to mark the traditional New
Year (from April 12 to 14), wishing peace, development and
prosperity for the country and the people.  
