<HEADLINE> Michael Chang Wins Salem Open Tennis in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 14 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Michael Chang beat
Australia's fifth-seeded Patrick Rafter 6-3, 6-3 in an unusual
final to take his third Salem Open tennis tournament title here
Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Chang, a Chinese-American now ranked third in the world, was
the winner of the annual Hong Kong event in 1994 and 1995 and he
lost to compatriot Pete Sampras in the final last year.
</P>
<P>
Chang led the match 6-3, 5-3 (40-15 in the ninth game) when
rain forced the organizers first to suspend and then, after hours'
waiting for weather to improve, postpone the play Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
After the game was resumed this morning, Rafter narrowed the
gap to 40-30 with a high volley but lost one more point which then
sealed up Chang's victory.
</P>
<P>
Both of them said that they would try to come back next year.
</P>
