<HEADLINE> Italian Zanardi Wins Long Beach IndyCar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Italian Allessandro Zanardi
won the Long Beach Grand Prix CART IndyCar race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Zanardi, 30, took the lead on lap 94 when his teammate,
defending champion Jimmy Vasser, had to make a last pit stop for
fuel.
</P>
<P>
Zanardi averaged 151.33 kph in a Reynard Honda, beating
Brazil's Mauricio Gugelmin in a Reynard Mercedes-Benz by 3.82
seconds in the 105-lap race around the 2.56-km temporary road
circuit.
</P>
<P>
American Scott Pruett, winner at Surfers Paradise, Australia,
last week, finished third in a Reynard Ford.
</P>
<P>
The fourth race in the 17-race series will take place on April
27 at the 1.6 km oval at Nazareth, Pennsylvania. 
