<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Carvalho Retains Rio Marathon Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Elisvaldo
Rodrigues Carvalho outpaced some 2,000 runners to win the Rio
Marathon Sunday for the second consecutive year.
</P>
<P>
Carvalho covered the 42.195-kilometer course in two hours 19
minutes and 39 seconds, nearly three minutes slower than his time
last year.
</P>
<P>
Compatriot Francismar de Barros finished second in 2:19:50.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Luciene Soares took the women's event in 2:49:34 by
beating favorite Nercy Freitas with ease.
</P>
<P>
Freitas, running in her 45th marathon and a three-time Rio
marathon winner, finished third in 2:52:45 behind Arlete Soares in
2:52:29.
</P>
<P>
With his victory, Carvalho obtained a berth for the New York
City Marathon later this year.
</P>
<P>
The race was billed as the first Iberian-American marathon and
attracted runners from Brazil, Spain, Portugal and Colombia.
</P>
</TEXT>
