<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Poland Sign Agreement on Scientific </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Poland signed
here today an agreement on scientific and cultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, which is to cover three years beginning this
year, was signed by Secretary General of the Kuwaiti National
Council of Culture, Arts and Letters Suleiman Al-Askari and Polish
ambassador to Kuwait Jan Natkanski.
</P>
<P>
Al-Askari said after the signing ceremony that the program,
which covers cultural, art, media, educational and scientific
research fields, reflected the wishes of the two countries to
develop cooperation in the cultural and scientific domains.
</P>
<P>
The accord would boost cooperation between cultural
establishments, exchange of exhibitions, translation of literary
works and exchange of expertise and researches between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that such an agreement was signed by
the two countries. The first three-year accord was signed in
1990, but it was not implemented due to the Iraqi invasion of
Kuwait. 
</P>
</TEXT>
