<HEADLINE> Food to be Distributed in Northern Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Distribution of foodstuffs in
northern Iraq will begin next week, a U.N. source disclosed here
today.
</P>
<P>
The source said at a press conference that distribution of
flour in accordance with the U.N.-Iraqi oil-for-food deal will
take place in the three Kurdish-populated provinces of Dahook,
Arbil and Sulaimaniya at a rate of six kilograms per person.
</P>
<P>
The source added that nine U.N. observers in charge of
supervising the food distribution arrived in northern Iraq to
participate in the operation, together with specialized U.N.
agencies.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi Ministry of Commerce had embarked early April on
the distribution of flour among the Iraqi people as part
of the oil-for-food agreement, which permits Iraq to sell 2
billion U.S. dollars worth of oil over six months to finance the
purchase of foodstuffs, medicines and other basic necessities.
</P>
<P>
So far, about 300,000 tonness of foodstuffs, mostly wheat,
arrived in Iraq. Twelve cargo ships carrying foodstuffs are due
to arrive in Iraq this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
