<HEADLINE> Bahrain Decides to Establish Aid Committee to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain, one of the oil-rich
Gulf states, decided today to set up a special committee to
help Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
As part of the efforts by the island state to support
Palestinians, the Bahraini cabinet decided during a weekly
meeting held in the Bahraini capital of Manama today to establish a
national committee to provide humanitarian aid for Palestinian
people, Bahraini news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The decision came amid anti-Israel protests by Palestinians in
the West Bank town of Hebron because of Israel's settlement
policy in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain has blasted the Israeli housing policy and stressed
its support for Palestinian people after Israel decided to build
6,500 new houses in Har Homa in East Jerusalem, which
Palestinians want to be the capital of their future state.
</P>
<P>
The committee called National Committee For Supporting
Jerusalem was headed by Bahrain's Minister for Justice and
Islamic Affairs Sheikh Abdullah Bin Khaled al-Khalifa.
</P>
<P>
It was the second special committee established in the Gulf
region for helping Palestinians since Israel starting
construction of the Har Homa settlement last month.
Qatar set up a similar one named Defending Jerusalem
earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Observers noted that other Gulf states such as Saudi Arabia
and the United Arab Emirates (UAE) have also taken measures to
support Palestinians. 
</P>
