<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- More than a hundred
fire-fighters in southern Michigan worked for more than 12 hours to
put out a blaze at a solvent factory Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The fire at the Oak International plant in hundred was
punctuated by a series of exploding 55-gallon drums rocketing into
the air, the United Press International reported.
</P>
<P>
