under control until about 12:45 p.m. Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Oak International makes petroleum products, including
lubricants and solvents. Fire-fighters say no one was inside the
plant at the time of the fire.
</P>
<P>
Damage from the blaze was estimated at 2 million dollars,
including damage to the building and its contents.
</P>
<P>
Investigators will begin tracking down the cause of the fire
Monday morning.  
