<HEADLINE> Two Blasts Kill One and Injure Over 40 in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and 42
others were injured by two bomb blasts in Ethiopia's capital
Addis Ababa Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
The two bomb blasts happened almost simultaneously around
19:47. One blast which took place at Tegrie Hotel at the Piazza
Commercial Center killed one person and injured 34 others.
Another blast which occurred in an Italian restaurant named
Bluetop injured eight foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The two blasts happened just several hours after Ethiopian
Prime Minister Meles Zenawi returned to Addis Ababa after
completing his five-day visit to Italy.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's official media has not reported the two accidents
so far. The police is investigating the two blasts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
