<HEADLINE> Meningitis Kills 100 in East Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of the dreaded
cerebral spinal meningitis (CSM) in Koma, eastern Nigeria's
Adamawa state, has claimed 100 lives during the last five weeks.
</P>
<P>
The shortage of CSM vaccine in Koma interland and bad roads
for sending required drugs there, are the reasons for the rapid
spread of the disease, the local newspaper Sunday Tribune
reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The Koma people were dying in droves without any medical
facilities to alleviate the situation, said the newspaper, adding
that there was also no water and education facilities in
Komaland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
