<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mkapa Praises Nyerere for Distinguished Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(By Pei Shanqin)
</P>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 13 (Xinhua) -- President Benjamin Mkapa
today praised Mwalimu Julius Nyerere for his distinguished and
exemmplary services to Tanzania and African continent as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He said that Tanzanians should honour him by implementing and
upholding all the good things he has left, particularly peace and
nationalism in the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during celebrations to mark 75th birthday of Mwalimu
Nyerere, held at Diamond Jubilee Hall in Dar es Salaam this
evening, President Mkapa said the third phase government will
strive to ensure that liberty, unity, peace, nationalism and
self-reliance, among others, are maintained.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa described Mwalimu Nyerere as an unique leader who spent
his lifetime working to improve the lives of the people not only
in Tanzania but Africa as a whole and who did not work for self
aggrandizement.
</P>
<P>
He told over 1,000 guests who attended the brithday tea party
that despite the liberisation of the economy, the government was
determined to bring development to all Tanzanians and avoid
having the haves and have-nots which he said were source of riots
and peace destablization in many societies.
</P>
<P>
The president appealed to Tanzanians to support the government
in maintenance of peace, tranquility and unity, which, he said,
has earned the nation a lot of respect, and a point of referene
by many countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to youths, civil servants and young politicians to
read the country's history and understand it for them to be able
maintain the existing peace and unity which Mwalimuu Nyerere and
other retired leaders and politicians worked so hard to get.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the Tanzanians were born after independence and did
not participate or witness the struggle for this independence
which was fielded by Mwalimu Nyerere. "From expressions and deeds
there are people who think that independence came like rain, so I
advise, youths, young politicians and civil servants to read the
history for them to appreciate and value this peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
In respect to work done by the old people in the country, he
said, he has put in place arrangement of meeting elders in all
regions he toured and asked other leaders to do the same.
</P>
<P>
President Mkapa also said during his tenure of office he will
work towards making the country less dependent on foreign aid,
which he said has been Mwalimu's life dream.  
</P>
</TEXT>
