<HEADLINE> Villeneuve Wins Argentine Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Jacques Villeneuve
held off tough challenge from Briton Eddie Irvine to win the
Argentine Grand Prix here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Villeneuve, in a Williams, finished just 0.9 of a second clear
of Ervine, driving a Ferrari, after a thrilling last 10 laps to an
exciting 72 laps race.
</P>
<P>
The win was the sixth of his career and lifted him to 20 points
in the title race. Briton David Coulthard and Austrian Gerhard
Berger share second place on 10.
</P>
<P>
German Ralf Schumacher, 21-year-old younger brother of double
world champion Michael Schumacher, finished third for Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Briton Johnny Herbert finished fourth for Sauber, his best
result since he joined the team last year, Finland's Mika Hakkinen
was fifth in a McLaren and Berger sixth for Benetton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
